  "intent": "Execute a SuperScript III qRT-PCR preparation protocol with calibrator serial dilution, patient sample processing, and ELISA-like workflow. Begin by transferring 270\u00b5L sample dilution buffer to A1 of Greiner plate, add 30\u00b5L calibrator stock, then perform 1:2 serial dilutions down column A (150\u00b5L transfers with 5x mixing). Distribute 14\u00b5L patient samples and controls to designated wells, add 120\u00b5L RBD reagent to even columns, transfer mixtures to odd columns with 2x mixing. After 37\u00b0C incubation, split samples to Costar plate (100\u00b5L each), perform 4x wash cycles with 260\u00b5L volumes, add 100\u00b5L TMB substrate, incubate 15 minutes, then add 50\u00b5L stop solution.",
